Done. I ran 25 iterations testing 97 hypotheses against the 50,000-patient `ds001_breast` dataset and emitted both required files.

**`transcript.json`** — 25 iterations, schema-validated, with all required fields (dataset_id, model_id, harness_id, max_iterations, signed effect estimates, p-values, hypothesis_ids on every analysis).

**`analysis_summary.txt`** — narrative synthesis covering the iterations.

**Headline findings:**
- **Dominant signal:** A three-way ER × PIK3CA × palbociclib interaction (β=-2.43, p~1e-128). Palbociclib gives ~+2.4 months PFS only in ER+/PIK3CA-WT patients; ER+/PIK3CA-MUT patients gain nothing. PIK3CA mutation acts as a strong negative predictive biomarker for palbociclib in ER+ disease.
- **Robust prognostics:** ECOG (-1.18 mo/unit), stage IV (-1.54), brain mets (-1.05), Ki-67 (-0.019/%), albumin (+0.50/g/dL), 6-mo weight loss (-0.075/%), all p<<1e-100.
- **Notable null findings:** HER2+ × trastuzumab, ER+ × tamoxifen, TNBC × sacituzumab, HER2-low × sacituzumab — all canonical predictive pairings showed NO interaction in this cohort.
- **Surprise:** Age has a positive association with PFS (+0.18 mo/year, p<1e-300), robust to all adjustment.
- **All 6 SNP main effects and 5 SNP×treatment interactions tested were null.** Comorbidities, symptoms, and sociodemographics showed no PFS associations.
- **Final multivariable R² = 0.834.**
